173
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:44,480
And I uttered a prayer, Lord, just let me get out of here before he speaks to me or

174
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:44,980
to Eric.

175
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,760
As I drew close to the man, I turned my back,

176
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:51,020
trying to kind of sidestep him

177
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:53,900
and even avoid the very air that he might be breathing.

178
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:57,040
And as I did, Eric leaned over my arm

179
00:12:57,040 --> 00:13:01,660
and reaching with both arms in a baby's kind of that pick-me-up position.

180
00:13:02,570 --> 00:13:04,170
And before I could stop him,

181
00:13:05,540 --> 00:13:10,740
Eric had propelled himself from my arms into the man's arms.

182
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:16,200
And Eric, in an act of total trust, of love and submission,

183
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:19,960
he laid his tiny head upon the ragged man's shoulders.

184
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:25,170
And the man's eyes closed, and I saw tears hover beneath his lashes.

185
00:13:25,830 --> 00:13:30,250
And his aged hands, full of grime and pain and hard labor,

186
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:37,270
they gently, so gently, cradled my baby's bottom and stroked his back.

187
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:42,360
and the old man rocked and cradled Eric in his arms for a moment

188
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:44,460
and then his eyes opened

189
00:13:44,460 --> 00:13:47,360
and he sat squarely on my eyes

190
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:50,260
and he said in a firm commanding voice

191
00:13:50,260 --> 00:13:52,500
you take care of this baby

192
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:54,750
and somehow I managed

193
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,010
I will

194
00:13:56,010 --> 00:13:58,850
from a throat that contained a stone

195
00:13:58,850 --> 00:14:02,360
and I received my baby and the man said

196
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,560
God bless you ma'am

197
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:06,460
you've given me my Christmas gift

198
00:14:06,460 --> 00:14:09,080
and I ran to the car

199
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,380
My husband wondered why I was crying and saying,

200
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:15,520
My God, my God, forgive me.

201
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:19,780
Because the ragged old man had willingly reminded me

202
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:24,360
to enter the kingdom of God we must become as little children.

203
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:30,780
God can use the most unlikely of people

204
00:14:30,780 --> 00:14:35,240
to teach us the most profound truths about life.

205
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:40,080
He can do the same for you, the same for me.

206
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,960
Here he used the shepherds.

207
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:48,040
He used the shepherds to teach us something.

208
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,460
And what did those shepherds do?

209
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:53,500
The outcasts, what did they do?

210
00:14:53,980 --> 00:14:56,620
After they heard the message, they took a journey.

211
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:00,300
And what did they do?

212
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,340
They did two things.

213
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:05,730
The shepherds praised and proclaimed.

214
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:11,120
They praised God and they proclaimed the message.

215
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:17,600
In other words, they worshiped and they witnessed after experiencing God.

216
00:15:19,660 --> 00:15:26,260
They made that journey from the countryside into town to see the baby, and they gave him homage.

217
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:28,960
It says they knelt at the manger.

218
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:34,930
And after worshiping and giving God praise, they went out to witness.

219
00:15:34,930 --> 00:15:36,890
It says they went out to proclaim.

220
00:15:37,130 --> 00:15:42,500
They went, so to speak, to tell it on the mountain that Jesus Christ is born.

221
00:15:44,620 --> 00:15:48,180
this rough, ragtag group of social outcasts,

222
00:15:49,180 --> 00:15:52,860
these men were the first evangelists.

223
00:15:54,740 --> 00:15:55,360
Isn't that amazing?

224
00:15:56,650 --> 00:16:02,840
The first evangelists were the ragtag social outcasts, the shepherds.

225
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:08,120
Shepherds realized they were important to God.

226
00:16:09,660 --> 00:16:12,560
The angel of the Lord came to the people who were outcasts.

227
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:16,880
They realized they were important to God.

228
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:18,900
And they went to worship.

229
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:20,060
They gave God everything.

230
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,400
They gave Him their total homage.

231
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:25,630
And from their worship, they went to tell the world.

232
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,180
Friends, that's our journey as well.

233
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:33,690
We are to respond how to God.

234
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:37,650
When God gets a hold of us, we're to respond, number one, in worship.

235
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:40,890
And from our worship comes our witness.

236
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:48,160
As God teaches us who He is, we're overwhelmed and we tell the world

237
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:52,660
that the message is not just for us, but for everyone who would believe.

238
00:16:54,140 --> 00:16:59,650
And if he can use shepherds, he can certainly use all of you, all of us.

239
00:17:02,860 --> 00:17:03,940
We tell the world what?

240
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:07,440
We tell the world that our sins can be forgiven.

241
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:10,180
We tell the world that God loves us.

242
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:13,620
We tell the world that we can have a new start in life

243
00:17:13,620 --> 00:17:17,600
and that we can know God and enjoy him forever.

244
00:17:18,590 --> 00:17:20,190
That's what we tell the world.

245
00:17:21,090 --> 00:17:22,610
That's the message of Christmas.

246
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:30,560
Another way to understand this message is in this great story.

247
00:17:32,470 --> 00:17:37,050
It was a preacher's family setting up the nativity scene in the front yard.

248
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:42,680
And all of them were carrying out those little statues to put in the scene.

249
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:46,420
You know, Mary and Joseph and the manger and the baby.

250
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:51,220
And you've got the angels and the shepherds and all the barnyard animals.

251
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:58,330
The pastor says a little Scotty came out carrying his favorite toy.

252
00:17:58,790 --> 00:18:02,490
the figure of the fierce Tyrannosaurus rex,

253
00:18:04,260 --> 00:18:05,480
king of the dinosaurs.

254
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:09,610
It was one of those plastic figurines,

255
00:18:09,710 --> 00:18:12,230
the kind that you inflate, the kind that blow up.

256
00:18:12,270 --> 00:18:14,150
And I imagine it being a few feet high

257
00:18:14,150 --> 00:18:16,490
with the little arms sticking out and the big teeth.

258
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:18,690
You can imagine what it looks like.

259
00:18:20,420 --> 00:18:23,120
And in comparison, he says, to the other figurines,

260
00:18:23,220 --> 00:18:26,700
it was rather ominous, rather overpowering,

261
00:18:26,700 --> 00:18:29,320
standing tall above the rest of the scene.

262
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:34,000
And dad kept saying, Scotty, you've got to take that back in the house.

263
00:18:34,140 --> 00:18:35,560
It doesn't belong there.

264
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:39,980
Dinosaurs, you see, son, existed thousands of years beforehand.

265
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,280
It doesn't make sense to be in the nativity scene.

266
00:18:44,380 --> 00:18:45,260
But he insisted.

267
00:18:45,980 --> 00:18:46,760
Come on, dad.

268
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:49,700
Let the dinosaur be part of it.

269
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:56,900
And after insisting and probably making a scene there on the driveway, dad backed down.

270
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,420
And so they stood back.

271
00:18:59,420 --> 00:19:05,220
and there's that fierce dinosaur standing hovering over the entire nativity scene

272
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:14,280
and then dad had this insight he said maybe that dinosaur says more than we realize

273
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:23,530
because for over each of us is a menacing character that threatens to rob us of all of our joy and our

274
00:19:23,530 --> 00:19:32,530
peace and our cheer but christmas reminds us the baby in the manger is stronger than all the

275
00:19:32,530 --> 00:19:41,740
dinosaurs in our lives. And God has given us the victory through Jesus Christ, the one in the

276
00:19:41,740 --> 00:19:51,890
manger. And so, yes, the dinosaur belongs, but the baby triumphs. That's the message of Christmas.

277
00:19:54,330 --> 00:20:00,830
Molly Brown said, Christmas is love, tugging men's and women's hearts back to God with a powerful

278
00:20:00,830 --> 00:20:03,190
grip of a tiny hand

279
00:20:03,190 --> 00:20:05,190
reaching out from the bed of straw

280
00:20:05,190 --> 00:20:07,630
no matter what dinosaur

281
00:20:07,630 --> 00:20:08,930
might be over it

282
00:20:08,930 --> 00:20:10,700
that little baby

283
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:12,990
has the power to conquer

284
00:20:12,990 --> 00:20:15,940
and that's the message

285
00:20:15,940 --> 00:20:17,280
friends do you believe it

286
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:19,460
do you live it

287
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:21,860
and will you share it

288
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:24,420
for it is the greatest news in the world

289
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:26,650
that God loves you

290
00:20:26,650 --> 00:20:27,730
died for you

291
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:29,750
has given you his Holy Spirit

292
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:32,510
wants your worship and wants you to tell

293
00:20:32,510 --> 00:20:35,670
that message to the next person on the block

294
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:40,330
and in our neighborhood, in our communities, and literally

295
00:20:40,330 --> 00:20:44,240
around the world, that Jesus Christ has come

296
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:49,160
and we come to adore Him. And so my encouragement to you

297
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:53,060
is to have a very Merry Christmas. We're now going to stand and we're going to

298
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:56,080
sing, Go Tell It on the Mountain.

299
00:20:56,720 --> 00:21:00,840
And I want us not just to sing that because it's a quaint song, but because

300
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:05,520
it is the reality of our hearts this morning, that we are going to worship and pay homage

301
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:09,680
and tell the world that Jesus Christ has come.

302
00:21:10,710 --> 00:21:14,420
And so now, Dave, would you lead us as we sing, and let's stand together.

